properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 7 at 3:41AM EST until February 7 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, west winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts
up to 40 kt and seas 7 to 12 feet. For the Small Craft
Advisory, northwest winds 10 to 20 kt with gusts up to 25 kt
and seas 6 to 9 feet expected.

* WHERE...Nearshore Gulf waters from the Walton-Okaloosa County
line to the Ochlockonee River out 20 nautical miles, and
Nearshore Gulf waters from the Ochlockonee River to the
Suwannee River out 20 nautical miles.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 10 AM EST /9 AM CST/ this
morning. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 10 AM EST /9 AM
CST/ this morning to 7 PM EST /6 PM CST/ this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
